      "id": "VL_SurvivorJournal_Day4",
      "character": "Survivor_Journal_Day4",
      "text": "Day four. No rain. The river is dropping — I can see the mud flats now where the water used to be. That means the big ones will come to drink at the shallows. I need to move my camp before dark.",
      "url": "https://thdlkizjbpwdndtggleb.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/game-assets/tts/1782992138765_Survivor_Journal_Day4.mp3",
      "duration_estimate": "~13s",
      "trigger": "day_4_morning_journal",
      "context": "Player journal entry — environmental awareness, water source danger"
    },
    {
      "id": "VL_SurvivorTip_BirdScatter",
      "character": "Survivor_Tip_BirdScatter",
      "text": "Watch the sky before you move. Birds scatter before a predator — not during, before. If you see a flock lift from the trees all at once, something is already moving beneath them. Stop. Wait. Let it pass.",
      "url": "https://thdlkizjbpwdndtggleb.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/game-assets/tts/1782992155012_Survivor_Tip_BirdScatter.mp3",
      "duration_estimate": "~14s",
      "trigger": "first_time_near_forest_edge",
      "context": "Survival tip — predator awareness via environmental cues"
    }
  ],

